These incidents highlight the ongoing debate surrounding Rittenhouse's actions and the broader issue of free speech on university campuses.

name: Long Beach State basketball
summary: Long Beach State University's Men's Basketball team has made an impressive return to the March Madness NCAA Tournament. Despite the recent firing of head coach Dan Monson, the team, under his temporary leadership, has qualified for the tournament. In their first-round game, they faced the University of Arizona, ultimately losing 65-85. Despite the defeat, Monson's guidance has been praised, leading to speculation about his potential return to the coaching position. The team's unexpected success has garnered attention for its resilience and determination, showcasing their capabilities and potential in the tournament.

name: Warzone Mobile
summary: Call of Duty's long-awaited mobile version, Warzone Mobile, has officially launched worldwide. The game features a 120-player Verdansk map, cross-platform play, and a variety of gameplay modes. Activision has also announced a launch event called Operation: Day Zero. Despite its mobile platform, the game has received praise for its high-quality graphics, which are reportedly improved with extended playtime. Warzone Mobile aims to address the stigma surrounding mobile gaming by providing a console-like experience on a portable device. It is expected to be a major player in the mobile gaming market and potentially connect the franchise's PC, console, and mobile fan bases.

name: Dayton basketball
summary: The University of Dayton Flyers, seeded 7th in the NCAA Tournament, faced the 10th-seeded Nevada Wolf Pack in the first round. Despite a close game, Dayton managed to secure a 63-60 victory. The game was live-streamed and aired on ESPN, and highlights are available on NCAA.com. Nevada had a strong start, but Dayton rallied in the second half to avoid Nevada's upset bid. Experts and fans alike highlighted three keys to Dayton's victory: rebounding, defense, and free throw shooting.

name: Tennessee basketball
summary: Tennessee's basketball team faced a disappointing end in the SEC tournament quarterfinals, with a 73-56 loss to 9th-seeded Mississippi State. This defeat dashed their hopes of securing the No. 1 seed in the NCAA Tournament. In the upcoming March Madness tournament, Tennessee has been given a No. 2 seed and will face Saint Peter's in their opening game. Rick Barnes and his players have expressed their reactions to the team's seeding. Meanwhile, Mississippi State's victory marked a stunning upset over the 5th-ranked Volunteers.
